snippet.textDisplay:
-The old death sounds

-An option between grunts and voice acting

-The Mos Eisley Cantina from TCS and maybe also the one from Lego Star Wars II: The Original Trilogy.

-Better character customisation (I'm sure they'll implement this improved mechanic from the recent LEGO games, they're pretty robust.)

-Better cheats (TCS really improved on the cheats after the original 2 LEGO Star Wars games. They should try implementing some of the cheats to the new game.)

-Better combat system (To be honest, they downgraded the lightsaber combat in LEGO Star Wars III: The Clone Wars and TFA, with just constant buttons mashing. Although in the original games is almost the same exact thing, you can do combos, but with the right timing. I think it's similar to The Force Unleashed, when the lightsaber flashed when you attack.)

-Classic character models from TCS as an option.

They better not mess this up. I've never seen a LEGO game with this amount of hype, just because of The Complete Saga. Gonk.
